      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a quiet, terrifying freedom to let the mask fall off when there's no one left to please. If the performance is just a hollow echo, then stopping it isn't a failure—it's the only honest thing you can do. The point of keeping up the charade was to hide the emptiness, but now that you've seen it, the only way to stop hurting is to finally let go of the act entirely.",
